<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include('../partials/head') %>
        <title>Privacy Policy - Paybilupi</title>
</head>

<body class="bg-mesh font-outfit d-flex flex-column min-vh-100">
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-white border-bottom border-light py-3">
        <div class="container">
            <a class="navbar-brand d-flex align-items-center gap-2" href="/">
                <div class="bg-primary bg-gradient text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center shadow-sm"
                    style="width: 36px; height: 36px;">
                    <i class="fi fi-rr-wallet fs-5 mt-1"></i>
                </div>
                <span class="fw-bold fs-4 tracking-tight text-main">Paybilupi</span>
            </a>
            <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
                <a href="/auth/login" class="btn btn-alt px-4 rounded-pill fw-semibold shadow-sm d-none d-sm-block">Sign
                    In</a>
                <a href="/auth/register" class="btn btn-premium px-4 rounded-pill fw-semibold shadow-sm">Get Started</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <div class="container py-5 my-5 flex-grow-1">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-9">
                <div class="mb-5 border-bottom border-light pb-4" data-aos="fade-up">
                    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-main mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-0">Last updated: February 28, 2026</p>
                </div>

                <div class="premium-card p-4 p-md-5" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
                    <p class="text-muted mb-5">At Paybilupi, we take your privacy and data security incredibly
                        seriously. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of personal data we collect, how it is used,
                        and the steps we take to ensure your data remains protected when you use our payment
                        orchestration software, mobile applications, and API services (collectively, the "Services").
                    </p>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">1. Information We Collect</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-3"><strong>Information you provide to us:</strong> When you register for an
                        account, we collect identifying information such as your name, corporate email address, business
                        name, and business address.</p>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-3"><strong>Gateway Credentials:</strong> To facilitate zero-fee routing, we
                        temporarily process and securely store encrypted metadata linking to external wallets (e.g.,
                        your PhonePe/Paytm mobile numbers or merchant tokens). <em>We never store consumer banking
                            passwords or full credit card numbers on our servers.</em></p>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-5"><strong>Transaction Metadata:</strong> When you generate payment links or
                        use the API, we log transaction referrers, IP addresses, localized order amounts, and order
                        statuses to populate your analytics dashboard.</p>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">2. How We Use Information</h4>
                    <ul class="text-muted mb-5" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                        <li>To provision your merchant account and authenticate API requests.</li>
                        <li>To route transactions to your connected third-party gateways (PhonePe, Paytm).</li>
                        <li>To provide analytics, reporting, and webhook callbacks regarding payment statuses.</li>
                        <li>To detect, prevent, and mitigate fraudulent activity within the ecosystem.</li>
                        <li>To communicate critical system updates, schema changes, and service announcements.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">3. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-5">Paybilupi is not a data broker. We do not sell your personal data. Data
                        is only shared with third-party gateway partners explicitly when you initiate a connection
                        request to them from your dashboard (for example, triggering a PhonePe OTP). We may also
                        disclose data locally to law enforcement agencies if mandated by a valid, legally-standing
                        Indian court order.</p>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">4. Security Measures</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-5">All data exchanged between your servers and ours is transmitted over
                        modern TLS cryptographic protocols (HTTPS). Sensitive database entries, including your gateway
                        access tokens, are hashed and encrypted at rest utilizing AES-256 standards. However, no
                        internet-based service can guarantee 100% security against zero-day exploits.</p>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">5. Data Retention</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-5">We retain transaction metadata and account information indefinitely to
                        support dispute resolution and your historical analytics dashboard unless you explicitly request
                        account deletion. Upon account deletion, standard transaction logs may be retained for up to 7
                        years to comply with financial auditing regulations.</p>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">6. Cookies and Tracking</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-5">The Paybilupi dashboard utilizes first-party session cookies exclusively
                        to maintain your authentication state and secure you against Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF).
                        We do not deploy third-party advertising trackers on the merchant portal.</p>

                    <h4 class="fw-bold text-main mb-3">7. Contact Us</h4>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-0">If you have any questions or concerns navigating this Privacy Policy or
                        concerning the handling of your data, please contact our Data Protection Officer immediately at
                        <a href="mailto:privacy@paybilupi.com"
                            class="fw-bold text-primary text-decoration-none">privacy@paybilupi.com</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>

</html>